hich are maintaining hygiene, social decorum, appearance, and life time of the fabric. In industrialised countries, laundry is done with detergents using appliances such as tunnel washers or domestic washing machines, at temperatures well above room temperature using treated/purified water. In developing countries, often it is done by hand washing with water from local sources and some form of detergents. In both the cases, the detergent wastes are finally exposed to environment. Laundering is affected by four factors, often called Sinner's factors: (a) chemicals/detergents (b) temperature (c) time/duration (d) mechanical. It is an energy intensive and water consuming process, and the surfactants are often contaminative to ecosystem. By designing detergents with more than one surfactants, which acts synergistically, it is possible to (a) reduce the energy consumption by reducing washing temperature, (b) use less amount of water and (c) use less amount of detergent- all three are key for sustainability.</gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2013-08-21</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/organisation/798CB33D-C79E-4578-83F2-72606407192C"><gtr:id>798CB33D-C79E-4578-83F2-72606407192C</gtr:id><gtr:name>EPSRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2010-02-22</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>313071</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs/><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs><gtr:impactSummaryOutput><gtr:description>The findings were used in the collaboration between Croda and Unilever to develop new detergent for the market.</gtr:description><gtr:firstYearOfImpact>2014</gtr:firstYearOfImpact><gtr:id>562B4043-F3AC-4123-8710-6E3A6F866A5B</gtr:id><gtr:impactTypes><gtr:impactType>Economic</gtr:impactType></gtr:impactTypes><gtr:sector>Chemicals</gtr:sector></gtr:impactSummaryOutput></gtr:impactSummaryOutputs><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:description>Within the project new ways to characterise surface activity of detergents with the focus on new sustainable detergents extracted from renewable sources were developed. The physical method on which the characterisation is based on is the measurement of surface interaction potentials using a Photonic Force Microscope. From these measurements a characteristic surface affinity could be assigned to different detergents related to environmental conditions and fabric type.</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>The research was done for a specific industrial application. The project was in collaboration with the companies Croda and Unilever, which will use the results in future.</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>2DD87159-1DA4-4F66-BEBF-A9A5BA672FAC</gtr:id><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Chemicals,Environment</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/5CB412D3-E6DC-425C-A021-DF04E02E02D0"><gtr:id>5CB412D3-E6DC-425C-A021-DF04E02E02D0</gtr:id><gtr:title>A Physics approach to chemical surface modification</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/62793a2065277fbaafee25f7f42310c5"><gtr:id>62793a2065277fbaafee25f7f42310c5</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Heinrich Hoerber (Author)</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2012-01-01</gtr:date></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/89D5926B-9048-4F7E-9177-922B92F9B9D6"><gtr:id>89D5926B-9048-4F7E-9177-922B92F9B9D6</gtr:id><gtr:title>Molecular Surface Interactions</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/62793a2065277fbaafee25f7f42310c5"><gtr:id>62793a2065277